```
In this code just above, an error is shown if the Company Name exists.  If it doesn&#39;t yet exist then the wizard this component resides in will advance forward.  The key takeaway here is that all of the logic to handle the response is contained in the `useEffect`.

This all works fine unless the user enters the same Company Name twice in a row.  In this particular case, the `url` dependency in the `companyFetch` instance of `useFetch` does not change and thus there is no new request sent to the API Endpoint.

I can think of several ways to try to solve this but they all seem like hacks.  I&#39;m thinking that others must have encountered this problem before and am curious how they solved it.

